    {
      "para_id": "Q001556.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) After having built Ninĝirsu's E-ninnu , Gudea , ruler of Lagaš , Ninĝirsu's true shepherd of reliable words , who ( always ) perfoms the rituals of the gods correctly , exempted Namḫani , the chief lamentation singer of the E-munus-gisa . from anyone entering his house ( with claims for ) for silver , bronze , corvée labour , ( or ) whatever property he has . In that year ( Gudea ) assigned an area of 6 bur ... field to him ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001556.21",
      "line_range": "21",
      "translation": "(iii 2) .... He set it up for her in the E-munus-gisa on the appointed day . The name of this statue is \" Gudea gave it to me .\""
    }
  ],
